\newlabel{fig:toy_cg_kappa}{{5}{20}{Toy unpreconditioned CG over a range of condition numbers $\kappa $, comparing FP32 and FP64. At $\kappa = 10$ the two precisions track each other exactly; for $\kappa \gtrsim 10^{3}$ FP32 loses orthogonality and stalls. This is the Mukunoki--Ozaki regime, in which precision buys \emph {fewer iterations}---and the regime our eo-preconditioned DWF tests do \emph {not} sit in}{figure.5}{}}
