\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces FP64-base multiword: true-residual descent for FP, DW, and TW. The triple-double constant pipeline yields three cleanly separated floors ($1.59\times 10^{-30}$ / $1.03\times 10^{-62}$ / $8.57\times 10^{-76}$), tens of orders below native FP64, with no breakdown.}}{23}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:double_base}{{6}{23}{FP64-base multiword: true-residual descent for FP, DW, and TW. The triple-double constant pipeline yields three cleanly separated floors ($1.59\times 10^{-30}$ / $1.03\times 10^{-62}$ / $8.57\times 10^{-76}$), tens of orders below native FP64, with no breakdown}{figure.6}{}}
